
1.  What is/are the problem/s you want to solve? Please provide background based on research. 
A lot of time we find ourselves with some leftover ingredients not knowing what to do with them. This mobile app will let the users come up quickly with a recipe that will make the best use of the leftovers. With the help of this application, people will not have to waste as much spare product as we do now, instead we will be able to get decent meal out of them.

2.  Who are the users you are targeting? Please use a Persona to describe your users and draw a picture of your target user. 
Our mobile application will target, anyone with an android smartphone. The user will look for people who are not making a lot of money to the point where they can eat out or hire a chef. The targeted user will a working type who is on a tight budget and enjoys home cooking.

3.  What are the major features of the solution? List the features.
The major features of the solution are the home page and the landing page. The home page allows a user to input 3 search terms, which will be ingredients. The landing page retrieves recipes from an API and gives the user a clean interface to scroll through the different recipes.

4.  How is this solution unique? How does it relate to existing solutions on the market? What are 5 solutions similar or related to what you want to do in the Google Play Store. Do the research and know that you are probably not reinventing the wheel!
As a result of a search on Google Play and on Google about cooking applications, most applications that come up when we typed recipes or cooking app are centered around the recipes themselves and the type of cuisine. Our application will look to get it users the best recipes for their inputted ingredients. Our selling point will be that, instead of telling the users what they should make, which will mostly likely lead them to spending more the ingredients, we will ask them what they had and give them a recipe accordingly.

